New LifeStyles Online houses a database of all state licensed senior communities, home health & hospice agencies nationwide, plus other non-licensed communities and senior products & services. You can view basic information on these companies, contact them through e-mail forms, get more information on them by linking to their sites, take an online tour of communities, download a brochure and more!  Being a family oriented company, New LifeStyles saw a need for a child care resource similar to their successful senior housing and care guide, thus, the creation of The Child Care Source.  The Child Care Source is a guide to child care options in Texas. their website, TheChildCareSource.com lists all licensed, registered, and listed child care options in Texas.  In 2007, New LifeStyles acquired the provider web site division from AssistGuide. We now host more than 300 websites focusing on senior-oriented businesses, but also including sites for child care providers, physicians, landscaping design, retailers, national associations and more.  New LifeStyles has an iPhone App specifically designed to find local senior communities. Visit the App Store to download it for free!  For those using a Blackberry or Android, New LifeStyles also offers a mobile site designed for easy searchability and ordering. Just visit www.newlifestyles.com on your smart phone to be directed to the mobile site.  New LifeStyles continues to grow offering the public and our clients more options.

Description: Stillwater Supercomputing designs and markets a hardware accelerator synthesis platform to create workload optimized hardware.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Stillwater Supercomputing, Inc. designs and markets a compute acceleration platform for computational science and knowledge discovery. The compute accelerator is based on a specialized semiconductor device called the Stillwater Knowledge Processing Unit, or KPU(TM). The KPU provides unmatched price/performance at ultra low power to expand the market for high-performance computing to the small and medium-sized enterprise.   The Stillwater business model is a pure fabless semiconductor business. That is, we design, market, and sell the KPU directly to cloud providers and IHVs. To create demand for the KPU, we work with cloud providers and ISVs to help the ISV enable the KPU in their software. We do this through a Platform-as-a-Service model, where Stillwater develops software components that encapsulate complex algorithms that are essential in computational science and digital game entertainment workloads. These components can be rapidly assembled into applications by the ISVs and deployed in the cloud.

Description: Tulsa's Green Country Staffing plays a key role for Tulsa during the economic recovery.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Tulsa's Green Country Staffing has opened its newly built 5000 sq/ft facility on Garnett Road near East 71st Street and Mingo Valley Expressway. Green Country Staffing has helped Tulsa employers find and hire qualified candidates since 1993. They realized over the last months that increasing demand from hiring companies and job seekers was quickly outgrowing their existing location. "They wanted to expand their ability to recruit, qualify and place good candidates and knew they would need to build a bigger facility with more advanced systems to accomplish this," said Mike Kelly, President and founder of Green Country. "At the new location they can provide electronic candidate screening, testing and placement, which allows us to quickly connect employers with the right person for each job." Candidates can apply for any one of many job openings managed through Green Country. Applications can be completed online or in person at the new facility. Skill testing is available to ensure that candidates meet the requirements of a particular job, allowing new hires and employers confidence that they'll be successful in the new position.
